{"id":"9712dc9b-41d4-4248-9dde-ecbe4a931c4a","slug":"how-to-create-article","title":"how to create article","category":"article","content":"Cloudflare Workers is a serverless computing platform that allows developers to run JavaScript, TypeScript, or WebAssembly code directly on Cloudflare’s global edge network. Instead of relying on traditional servers, applications can execute code closer to users, which significantly improves performance and reduces latency.\n\nOne of the major advantages of Cloudflare Workers is its scalability. Since the platform runs on Cloudflare’s distributed infrastructure, it can automatically handle large amounts of traffic without requiring developers to manage servers or infrastructure. This makes it ideal for building modern web applications, APIs, authentication systems, and edge-based services.","published":true,"createdAt":1773115287253,"updatedAt":1773115395654}